281
00:24:04,025 --> 00:24:05,944
We're on the same team, don't you want to be friends?

282
00:24:06,528 --> 00:24:07,946
I have an exam next week. I have to study.

283
00:24:08,363 --> 00:24:09,698
It's next week.

284
00:24:09,823 --> 00:24:11,450
There's still time. Relax a bit.

285
00:24:12,075 --> 00:24:13,952
Why are you so serious about everything?

286
00:24:14,494 --> 00:24:15,078
Listen

287
00:24:15,328 --> 00:24:17,414
some people don't have time to relax.

288
00:24:17,914 --> 00:24:19,458
If they don't take things seriously

289
00:24:19,916 --> 00:24:21,460
they might miss their chances.

290
00:24:25,088 --> 00:24:26,047
You don't get it.

291
00:24:26,506 --> 00:24:28,383
We're not all born equal, you know.

292
00:24:30,677 --> 00:24:31,553
What the hell?

293
00:24:32,512 --> 00:24:33,388
For me

294
00:24:33,889 --> 00:24:36,808
free food from others isn't as satisfying as the food I buy myself.

295
00:24:37,476 --> 00:24:38,602
Go treat someone else.

296
00:24:39,269 --> 00:24:40,437
I'm not hungry.

297
00:24:42,272 --> 00:24:43,273
Hey, wait!

298
00:24:44,816 --> 00:24:47,777
So, I won't treat you. We'll split the bill, okay?

299
00:24:48,528 --> 00:24:49,362
I'm hungry.

300
00:25:04,503 --> 00:25:05,420
Wow

301
00:25:06,546 --> 00:25:07,547
that looks so good.

302
00:25:08,632 --> 00:25:10,091
Do you always eat at fancy places or what?

303
00:25:11,134 --> 00:25:12,469
Don't exaggerate.

304
00:25:12,844 --> 00:25:14,471
I don't eat fancy meals everyday.

305
00:25:14,763 --> 00:25:16,473
I'm just an average middle-class guy.

306
00:25:17,933 --> 00:25:21,895
So, what class do you call someone who never eats anything fancy?

307
00:25:22,479 --> 00:25:24,773
You want to bring this up again.

308
00:25:25,941 --> 00:25:27,234
I just want you to think about it.

309
00:25:27,651 --> 00:25:30,237
For me and many others in this country

310
00:25:30,987 --> 00:25:33,240
this is an ordinary place where we eat every day.

311
00:25:34,074 --> 00:25:35,283
It doesn't get any fancier than this.

312
00:25:35,784 --> 00:25:37,744
Stir-fried basil with minced beef and fried egg is special enough

313
00:25:38,328 --> 00:25:39,371
beef is more expensive than other meat.

314
00:25:39,829 --> 00:25:42,916
Just regular beef, not wagyu, sirloin, or ribeye.

315
00:25:43,792 --> 00:25:45,502
The truth is

316
00:25:46,044 --> 00:25:49,172
there are classes above the ordinary and below the ordinary.

317
00:25:49,756 --> 00:25:51,508
When you never eat at places like this

318
00:25:51,967 --> 00:25:54,636
you are upper middle-class, above the ordinary.

319
00:25:55,178 --> 00:25:57,764
Okay, hold up.

320
00:25:58,265 --> 00:26:01,226
I know you're a sociology scholarship student

321
00:26:01,393 --> 00:26:03,061
and not some regular Joe.

322
00:26:03,436 --> 00:26:06,398
But right now I'm hungry, let's just eat, okay?

323
00:26:13,071 --> 00:26:13,780
Wow

324
00:26:14,573 --> 00:26:15,282
it's so spicy

325
00:26:15,865 --> 00:26:16,908
but so yummy!

326
00:26:19,578 --> 00:26:21,746
I warned you to tell them not to make it spicy.

327
00:26:22,914 --> 00:26:23,999
Well I wanted to try.

328
00:26:24,374 --> 00:26:25,375
Isn't it spicy for you?

329
00:26:28,128 --> 00:26:30,130
No problem. My tongue is used to it.

330
00:26:34,301 --> 00:26:34,968
For me

331
00:26:35,844 --> 00:26:37,262
this stir-fried basil with minced beef and fried egg

332
00:26:38,096 --> 00:26:39,014
is very special.

333
00:26:39,931 --> 00:26:41,266
It reminds me of something.

334
00:26:42,309 --> 00:26:43,268
What's that?

335
00:26:44,019 --> 00:26:46,980
That food and people are alike.

336
00:26:47,689 --> 00:26:50,734
To consider that a dish or a person is special or ordinary

337
00:26:51,526 --> 00:26:55,655
does not depend on class nor price

338
00:26:56,406 --> 00:26:57,365
but on...

339
00:26:58,491 --> 00:26:59,117
On what?

340
00:27:00,452 --> 00:27:03,413
It depends on what tastes good to you.

341
00:27:13,757 --> 00:27:15,300
They knew each other since university.

342
00:27:16,343 --> 00:27:17,761
Mek was an activist

343
00:27:18,136 --> 00:27:20,513
an athlete, a scholarship student

344
00:27:21,514 --> 00:27:23,099
nothing like me.

345
00:27:24,684 --> 00:27:26,353
what we had in common was we were poor

346
00:27:27,479 --> 00:27:28,813
struggling by ourselves.

347
00:27:37,864 --> 00:27:38,990
It's 11 p.m. already

348
00:27:41,743 --> 00:27:43,078
can I make my wish?

349
00:27:44,704 --> 00:27:45,955
You haven't finished your story.

350
00:27:46,373 --> 00:27:49,668
The rule is, you can only wish when it's exactly midnight

351
00:27:49,918 --> 00:27:50,710
remember?

352
00:27:52,170 --> 00:27:52,837
Hey

353
00:27:54,047 --> 00:27:55,298
I'm kinda hungry.

354
00:27:56,007 --> 00:27:57,384
Would you want to go get something to eat?

355
00:27:57,634 --> 00:28:00,595
You're hungry at this hour?

356
00:28:05,266 --> 00:28:06,726
Do you get hungry?

357
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:09,479
Of course

358
00:28:10,146 --> 00:28:12,273
I get hungry just like you.

359
00:28:13,858 --> 00:28:15,443
What do you want to eat?

360
00:28:16,486 --> 00:28:18,697
Stir-fried basil with minced beef and fried egg

361
00:28:26,538 --> 00:28:27,330
What?

362
00:28:27,831 --> 00:28:29,499
The story you told made me crave it.

363
00:28:30,291 --> 00:28:31,960
I'll take you to eat some other time.

364
00:28:32,335 --> 00:28:33,336
Now that's a promise.

365
00:28:34,212 --> 00:28:37,298
There are so many things I want to eat

366
00:28:38,007 --> 00:28:39,718
and so many places I want to go.

367
00:28:40,427 --> 00:28:41,803
So are you not from Bangkok?

368
00:28:42,470 --> 00:28:44,514
I mean...  when you were a human.

369
00:28:45,515 --> 00:28:46,266
No.

370
00:28:47,684 --> 00:28:49,144
From your accent

371
00:28:50,729 --> 00:28:53,690
I guess you're from somewhere...

372
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:56,735
I don't know. I can't tell.

373
00:28:57,110 --> 00:28:58,111
Take a guess.

374
00:29:00,739 --> 00:29:02,198
It seems like...

375
00:29:03,992 --> 00:29:05,577
you never stay anywhere for long.

376
00:29:07,036 --> 00:29:08,538
Are you a linguist?

377
00:29:09,497 --> 00:29:10,874
I majored in acting.

378
00:29:11,708 --> 00:29:14,461
I have a keen ear that catches accents, am I right?.

379
00:29:15,378 --> 00:29:16,004
You're right.

380
00:29:16,838 --> 00:29:19,048
I was born in some very distant province.

381
00:29:19,591 --> 00:29:22,594
Then when I was about 17 or 18, I moved somewhere else.

382
00:29:24,596 --> 00:29:25,597
Do you want me to guess more?

383
00:29:25,889 --> 00:29:26,723
Try.

384
00:29:29,601 --> 00:29:32,520
You finished high school and continued studying?

385
00:29:43,156 --> 00:29:44,324
Did I get it right?

386
00:29:46,367 --> 00:29:48,661
You're good at knowing other people's business.

387
00:29:48,995 --> 00:29:51,623
Hey, trying to say I'm nosy?

388
00:29:51,748 --> 00:29:52,916
I didn't say that.

389
00:29:53,208 --> 00:29:55,960
I'm just surprised that how come someone smart like you...

390
00:29:55,960 --> 00:29:58,004
Alright, that's enough. No more talk

391
00:29:59,380 --> 00:30:01,299
People always overlook their own problems

392
00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:03,176
until it's too late to fix them. Which is normal.

393
00:30:03,343 --> 00:30:04,719
Not too late!

394
00:30:06,137 --> 00:30:07,597
I see the problem now.

395
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:09,891
Do you want to hear more?

396
00:30:10,266 --> 00:30:12,644
Oh, yes. Let's hear it.

397
00:30:16,481 --> 00:30:18,191
As I said...

398
00:30:19,234 --> 00:30:21,069
I'm nothing like Mek

399
00:30:22,237 --> 00:30:23,363
except that we are both broke.

400
00:30:23,988 --> 00:30:26,241
That must be what Rain saw in me.

401
00:30:26,866 --> 00:30:28,326
He likes someone who fights for himself.

402
00:30:28,493 --> 00:30:29,410
Like I do.

403
00:30:31,120 --> 00:30:34,290
But Mek and I, we fight in different ways.

404
00:30:34,666 --> 00:30:39,712
The world outside our university is struggling with equal marriage rights, yet within our university walls

405
00:30:40,213 --> 00:30:42,549
there are issues even more unequal than that.

406
00:30:42,799 --> 00:30:45,301
It's as if for some group of people

407
00:30:45,593 --> 00:30:49,013
their time has stopped in the foregone era.

408
00:30:49,806 --> 00:30:52,976
According to the university's announcement in 2021

409
00:30:53,476 --> 00:30:57,105
dress codes for students are up to their gender identity

410
00:30:57,605 --> 00:31:01,359
or gender expression.

411
00:31:01,651 --> 00:31:06,239
This is meant to promote gender equality and against discrimination.

412
00:31:07,073 --> 00:31:09,576
However, this year, in 2023

413
00:31:09,868 --> 00:31:14,789
some professors still submitted complaints to the university administration

414
00:31:15,248 --> 00:31:17,500
and tried to stop our friends who don't conform to their birth gender

415
00:31:17,709 --> 00:31:20,503
from participating in various important university ceremonies.

416
00:31:21,254 --> 00:31:24,674
I consider this an act of destroying the announcement of the university council

417
00:31:24,966 --> 00:31:27,176
which is like our constitution.

418
00:31:27,427 --> 00:31:29,971
It is an assault on our rights, equality, and, most importantly

419
00:31:30,138 --> 00:31:32,849
an attack on democracy.

420
00:31:33,308 --> 00:31:36,269
Are we going to let a group of conservative professors misuse their power

421
00:31:36,603 --> 00:31:41,900
to destroy the progress we fought for so easily?

422
00:31:57,874 --> 00:32:00,209
Mek's influence resonated with Rain.

423
00:32:00,752 --> 00:32:03,046
They shared similar thoughts.

424
00:32:03,838 --> 00:32:05,048
From being friends

425
00:32:06,507 --> 00:32:07,550
they became lovers.

426
00:32:10,219 --> 00:32:13,765
Every evening, they'd head out to eat stir-fried basil with minced beef and fried egg together.

427
00:32:14,182 --> 00:32:16,851
Then they graduate and go separate ways.

428
00:32:17,560 --> 00:32:20,229
Rain worked in the corporate world briefly before leaving to open a coffee shop.

429
00:32:21,189 --> 00:32:22,190
As for Mek

430
00:32:23,107 --> 00:32:25,109
he became a full-time activist

431
00:32:25,944 --> 00:32:28,905
although he might not be adored much by some 'big' people.

432
00:32:33,701 --> 00:32:36,079
You really went into detail as if you were there yourself.

433
00:32:37,538 --> 00:32:40,083
Gotta thank Rain for his detailed notes

434
00:32:40,833 --> 00:32:43,127
and my job that requires imagination.

435
00:32:44,003 --> 00:32:47,757
So, are you saying that what you told me is partly from your own imagination?

436
00:32:48,424 --> 00:32:49,550
And yours too.

437
00:32:49,926 --> 00:32:50,802
I tell my story

438
00:32:51,177 --> 00:32:53,471
but if you don't use your imagination

439
00:32:53,805 --> 00:32:55,556
how can you see the picture?

440
00:32:56,933 --> 00:32:58,518
But you gotta give the credit to the storyteller.

441
00:32:59,102 --> 00:33:00,687
I'm an actor, remember that.

442
00:33:01,229 --> 00:33:03,398
I prefer to perform, rather than to write.

443
00:33:08,277 --> 00:33:09,237
You know

444
00:33:10,238 --> 00:33:11,990
I once thought about writing

445
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:14,701
jotting down events and feelings, like Rain did.

446
00:33:16,411 --> 00:33:17,829
I even bought this notebook.

447
00:33:19,789 --> 00:33:21,541
But until now, I haven't written a word.

448
00:33:28,089 --> 00:33:29,799
But you post on social media instead.

449
00:33:30,717 --> 00:33:31,426
Nope

450
00:33:32,510 --> 00:33:33,553
I use that for peeking

451
00:33:34,137 --> 00:33:35,138
not posting.

452
00:33:36,222 --> 00:33:37,890
Are all actors like you?

453
00:33:38,141 --> 00:33:40,309
Telling stories about others but keep their own hidden?

454
00:33:42,020 --> 00:33:43,438
Are you trying to insult me?

455
00:33:43,521 --> 00:33:45,773
No, I'm just curious.

456
00:33:46,315 --> 00:33:49,444
Why didn't I think about taking up acting or theatre?

457
00:33:50,319 --> 00:33:51,904
Can you teach me sometime?

458
00:33:54,490 --> 00:33:55,241
Okay

459
00:33:57,368 --> 00:33:58,661
but I'm strict.

460
00:34:02,623 --> 00:34:04,000
I'm a reaper.

461
00:34:05,001 --> 00:34:06,461
You think that scares me?

462
00:34:12,675 --> 00:34:13,718
Can I make my wish?

463
00:34:14,761 --> 00:34:17,096
You still haven't told me why Rain and Mek broke up.

464
00:34:18,681 --> 00:34:20,141
Rain didn't write it down.

465
00:34:20,725 --> 00:34:23,478
What I know is that Mek broke it off

466
00:34:24,020 --> 00:34:25,271
and Rain was heartbroken.

467
00:34:33,071 --> 00:34:36,866
Use that imagination of yours to help me visualize.

468
00:34:47,752 --> 00:34:48,961
What is it?

469
00:34:55,093 --> 00:34:56,177
Rain...

470
00:34:58,930 --> 00:34:59,889
let's end it.

471
00:35:04,644 --> 00:35:05,895
What do you mean?

472
00:35:08,314 --> 00:35:09,148
I...

473
00:35:13,611 --> 00:35:14,904
have someone else.

474
00:35:17,824 --> 00:35:18,533
Are you for real?

475
00:35:23,287 --> 00:35:24,747
Since when?

476
00:35:27,291 --> 00:35:28,167
For a while.

477
00:35:29,585 --> 00:35:30,628
Can you tell me

478
00:35:31,838 --> 00:35:32,880
who?

479
00:35:35,591 --> 00:35:36,467
And...

480
00:35:38,427 --> 00:35:39,679
you're sure you wanna know?

481
00:36:14,338 --> 00:36:18,009
Rain was heartbroken, until he met me.

482
00:36:18,676 --> 00:36:22,346
So Rain thought you could replace Mek.

483
00:36:23,514 --> 00:36:24,682
I thought so too

484
00:36:25,850 --> 00:36:27,018
like I said...

485
00:36:28,936 --> 00:36:30,855
Sometimes I look into his eyes

486
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:34,275
and I don't see myself there.

487
00:36:36,652 --> 00:36:37,653
But it was Mek.

488
00:36:54,712 --> 00:36:57,006
Wait, I have a question.

489
00:36:57,548 --> 00:36:58,090
What?

490
00:36:58,382 --> 00:36:59,425
So in the end

491
00:36:59,884 --> 00:37:01,219
did Mek really have someone else?

492
00:37:03,179 --> 00:37:04,013
Not bad...

493
00:37:04,722 --> 00:37:06,140
your question.

494
00:37:07,141 --> 00:37:08,434
The answer is...

495
00:37:09,018 --> 00:37:09,685
Yes.

496
00:37:10,144 --> 00:37:10,811
Who?

497
00:37:11,979 --> 00:37:12,897
He had the people.

498
00:37:13,481 --> 00:37:15,149
Rain found that out later.

499
00:37:17,485 --> 00:37:18,569
A true ideologist...

500
00:37:19,111 --> 00:37:20,821
I'm starting to respect him.

501
00:37:22,281 --> 00:37:24,992
If you're saying that a person who wants to change society

502
00:37:25,284 --> 00:37:28,329
to suit his own belief is an 'ideologist'

503
00:37:29,163 --> 00:37:34,585
then what about me struggling everyday to earn a living by doing what I love

504
00:37:34,752 --> 00:37:39,423
just trying to fit in this society and be happy is not considered to be an 'ideal' right?

505
00:37:41,259 --> 00:37:44,095
I believe we need to adapt to make it as a society.

506
00:37:45,346 --> 00:37:46,347
But Mek...

507
00:37:47,306 --> 00:37:48,724
he fights against society.

508
00:37:54,355 --> 00:37:57,108
Am I really going to erase him from this world?

509
00:37:57,566 --> 00:38:00,236
But that's your job, isn't it? Mr. reaper.

510
00:38:00,903 --> 00:38:05,908
I told you that I thought about it carefully this time.

511
00:38:06,325 --> 00:38:09,287
It will not cause repercussions for us to regret later.

512
00:38:10,329 --> 00:38:11,372
How so?

513
00:38:15,126 --> 00:38:16,460
He's already gone.

514
00:38:18,629 --> 00:38:21,048
You just make it so he never existed in this world in the first place

515
00:38:22,842 --> 00:38:24,260
Now I'm confused.

516
00:38:26,012 --> 00:38:27,930
After Rain started dating me

517
00:38:31,017 --> 00:38:32,810
there was news that Mek disappeared.

518
00:38:33,311 --> 00:38:35,104
What do you mean, disappeared?

519
00:38:36,314 --> 00:38:37,023
Yeah

520
00:38:38,566 --> 00:38:39,483
disappeared.

521
00:38:45,614 --> 00:38:47,158
I don't know if he ran away

522
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:50,202
or if someone... made him vanish.

523
00:38:51,871 --> 00:38:54,582
So, when he broke up with Rain, it was to save Rain.

524
00:38:56,834 --> 00:38:57,543
Probably.

525
00:39:00,212 --> 00:39:03,299
Then, do I have to make someone who has already disappeared disappear again?

526
00:39:05,134 --> 00:39:05,926
Yes, that's right.

527
00:39:06,260 --> 00:39:07,345
It's because of that darn Mek.

528
00:39:07,678 --> 00:39:10,931
Even though he's gone, He still exists in Rain's memories.

529
00:39:13,184 --> 00:39:14,018
You know what?

530
00:39:14,477 --> 00:39:18,397
If someone really did make him disappear, those people are evil.

531
00:39:19,106 --> 00:39:22,693
But you... you're going to make the world forget that he ever existed.

532
00:39:24,153 --> 00:39:25,571
You're even more evil!

533
00:39:45,758 --> 00:39:47,510
Here comes the hour of evil.

534
00:39:53,599 --> 00:39:55,309
I wish to...

535
00:40:22,837 --> 00:40:24,296
Today is the 9th of february 2023

536
00:40:24,463 --> 00:40:27,716
it will be five days until valentine's.

537
00:40:28,717 --> 00:40:29,760
That guy Earth has disappeared.

538
00:40:30,052 --> 00:40:33,097
Maybe today my duty might be over.

539
00:40:33,431 --> 00:40:37,560
No Earth, no Air, everything back to the way it was

540
00:40:38,144 --> 00:40:42,898
as if the clouds have parted and the sun is back to shine.

541
00:40:43,190 --> 00:40:45,943
Welcome, happy chocolate's day!

542
00:40:46,902 --> 00:40:47,945
What would you like sir?

543
00:40:48,612 --> 00:40:50,322
Is this a joke?
